<br>
On Shields, many of us put just 7 points into shield to get the engage skill as it's a great skill for so cheap.  You're running through the frontier alone or in a small group, you equip your shield.  Stealther smacks you with an arrow, just /face, engage, charge, switch back to DW and smack them around.  Though I must say this doesn't happen that often, it was more an issue months ago when archers ruled the world.  Another matter all together is the new popular 1-Hand/Shield Blademaster template (taking Shield instead of Celtic Dual).  I don't know much about that spec though so I can't comment.  I'd be curious what the advantages would be myself.  How is a 1H/Shield BM better than a 1H/Shield Hero/Champ? <p><p><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~cgbs/">Colonel</a>  <a href="mailto:cgbs@attbi.com"> Graydon Mithras</a><br>
