I have found some use for it in PBAE groups though. I know I have the blades skill to taunt quite well and keep a mob, but I often have a shield out to Guard the PB caster, and it has come in quite handy when someone else hasn't kept aggro, or the mage cast too soon.<br>
I am not loosing anything, as I am not the main damage dealer in the party here. I have lessened the amount of damage I take (not by much with only 7 shield skill, but a little), and I know that mage is loving it. If it is a single-pull group, I sometimes put Guard on a spear using hero or LW champ and they have enjoyed the extra protection.<br>
<br>
Advantages to a BM shield user as compared to a hero is that the BM has dexterity as a secondary stat, where the hero has it as tertiary. Your chance to block with a shield is modified by your dexterity, so a BM would be better with that shield. Whether this is a fully supportable idea, we will find out. Our guild currently has two pierce/shield BMs in training (pierce has an evade chain, and it's damage is partly dexterity based). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ugraydon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graydon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#000000>(10/21/02 10:31:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~cgbs/images/graydondaocm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: L40 Respec &amp; style help wanted</span><hr size=1> Got it.  Thanks, taliesin.  I always wondered what the appeal of the Shield BM was. <p><p><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~cgbs/">Colonel</a>  <a href="mailto:cgbs@attbi.com"> Graydon Mithras</a><br>
