<br>
I am not the main damage dealer here.<br>
I can hold aggro fine with only one weapon. This weapon in my off hand is just a timy bit of overkill.<br>
Why not use my shield?<br>
<br>
I started using the shield for PB groups because of this, and have never looked back.<br>
<br>
Sometimes I will not use it in this manner, if someone else has higher shield skill.<br>
<br>
If I am one of the main damage dealers (IE: main tank or all melee group), I need that extra damage from the off-hand weapon. Though on occasion I will still use the shield if the &quot;main tank&quot; is higher season than I am and uses LW or spear. In these cases, using the off hand weapon often ends up with me as the main tank, even though that was not the plan (even if the main is 2 or 3 seasons above me, is taunting, and I am not taunting.) Because of this I will use the shield to limit my damage output (now I will not be the main tank at all), and the main tank now has a little added protection.<br>
<br>
For my shield spec BM, I believe I will go with 44 in shield, pierce, and parry. The rest of the points will go into Celtic Dual only for a tiny bit more Flurry damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mpire667>mpire667</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#000000>(10/28/02 4:37:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: L40 Respec &amp; style help wanted</span><hr size=1> Thanks taliesin.<br>
That's great advice.<br>
<br>
This weekend I was in a CM group doing lodes and miners and I got to try this out, and it works exceptionally well.<br>
I had guard on the PB caster, and another tank had guard on me.<br>
I didn't have logging enabled (is there a way to have that enabled by default?) but just looking at the red status lines, the mobs (red and purple) rarely landed a hit on us, betwen evade, parry, block, guards and misses, our healer could have fallen asleep and we would have never known.<br>
<br>
I tried it solo, and it was somewhat successful, but no moreso than a CD beatdown, and took a lot longer. Might have saved me some health, but I wasn't blocking *that* much. Although getting off the 3 style block chain was cool.<br>
